=== Etymology ===
From {{L.}} [[cursus]], past participle of [[correre]] ''to run''

===Pronunciation===
*kôrs, /kɔː(r)s/, /kO:(r)s/
*{{audio|en-us-course.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɔː(r)s|-ɔː(r)s]]

====Homophones====
*[[coarse]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The itinerary of a race
#:''The cross-country '''course''' passes the canal''
# A period of learning
#:''I need to take a French '''course''' to pep up''
# A part of a meal
#:''We offer seafood as the first '''course'''''
# {{sports}} trajectory of a ball, Frisbee etc.
# (''boating'') The intended passage of voyage
#:''a '''course''' was plotted to traverse the ocean''
# (''bricklaying'') A row of bricks
# The path taken by a [[waterway]]

